At night, our camps are beset with the howls and cries of the local wildlife, namely the prowlers that come out of the woods to seek easy prey.
A nearby cave has been taken over by a massive, slumbering bear. Clear out the cave, so we can rest easier ourselves.
The Garden of Elune has fallen to terrifying shadow-creatures, including a night elf sorceress now known only as The Oracle.
For centuries, the Nightwatchers kept Nar'thalas safe and beautiful. Now, it's fallen to the naga, and even their own spirits turn against them.
It's one thing to have to camp in the middle of the woods, and it's another to wake full of tiny darts and surrounded by evil sprites.
Our sentries are terrified. At night, some great creature screeches and howls at them from the darkness. Seek out the terror that flaps in the night.
Faronaar is one of the Legion's most well-protected bastions in Azsuna. If we can take out some of their powerful demons, we will have the advantage.
The drogbar have burrowed their way out of the hills of Suramar, and are causing structural instability to the buildings in the area. We should root them out.
Outside the Moon Guard Stronghold, a siegemaster is blocking the way with a massive arcane siege weapon.
The Hall of the Guardian is established, but we are going to need more help. Archmage Omniara, a renowned Elemental Summoner, was just attacked!
Highmountain has a bear problem. Not just any bears, but bears cursed and corrupted by the harpies. We should cull them and end their suffering.
The Highmountain tauren have called for reinforcements to protect Thunder Totem from drogbar invaders. We should bolster their borders.
At the worst possible time, we have a worgen hunter who's gone mad. He's setting out traps for our allies. Hunt the hunter.
Along the coast of Azsuna, the Britterbrine raiders have collected and hoarded vast amounts of loot. We should see if we can claim any.
The Hatecoil hold an ace up their sleeves - if naga had sleeves. They have a massive creature, ready to summon at any moment. Destroy Golza.
The vrykul use runestones to summon powerful elementals, including Boulderfall, the Eroded, who can block the flow of rivers vital to the life of the valley.
In the Drowned Gardens of Azsuna, the Hatecoil naga have disturbed the souls of the Nightwatchers. Seek out and destroy their Stormbringer sorceress.
Dalaran is no stranger to attack, but sometimes the threat comes from within. A mage's experimental creature has escaped into the sewers.
Off the coast of Suramar, the naga have set up a stronghold. Below, Reef Lord Raj'his gathers a powerful army of ocean-dwellers.
The lion seals of Azsuna are taking up much of the viable shoreline and driving everyone away. Remove Ravyn-Drath, and the others will follow.
Some beasts don't wait for the cover of darkness to attack, and Abesha, a pale beast, has been stalking our allies in broad daylight. Dispose of the beast.
An attack squad of demons has emerged from Legion Camp: Chaos, and now threatens our allies in Azsuna. Seek out Lord Gorgamesh and his wyrmtongues.
Even other nightborne are afraid of Lilith the Terrible, who stalks the night with her dreaded Infiltrators. Face all fears, and dispose of Lilith.
Defending the borders of Suramar, Guardian Thor'el is sworn to attack anyone that approaches the city. Strike at the guardian to help clear a path.
The evil magic of the Nightmare has been seeping into the rivers of Val'sharah, and altered the aquatic life to a terrible degree.
The vrykul's long-dead ancestors rise from their graves, threatening our allies. Face the Nameless King, and put him back to rest.
Harpies love anything shiny, and the skywitches of Highmountain have stolen a piece of the vessel. Take it back, so we can set a trap for Hakkar.
A fragment of the vessel has fallen into the hands of Aughild the Bitter, a failed valkyra aspirant. Recover it from her, so we can set a trap for Hakkar.
Dark storms still gather above the Tomb of Sargeras, where the Legion army has gathered. Let us send our champions to the Broken Shore to scout the area and look for survivors.
Now that we have some recruits, we should deploy them in the field. A wrathguard, Valitos, leads a demon attack on Hearthglen. Let us send our champions to aid the citizens there.
The vrykul of Stormheim compete fiercely to win the favor of the Valkyra, and Isel the Hammer smiths their shields. We should remove her.
Wandering the remains of a ruined tower in Suramar, the nightborne Cadraeus threatens the roads and any travelers in the area.
Crab Rider Grmlrml seems to have found a new way of getting around. If it takes hold, we could be looking at an invasion of crab-riding murlocs.
In the Temple of a Thousand Lights, ancient mages still linger in the form of spirits and banshees. Destroy Arcanist Thinwhisp and her Ancient Flamecallers.
The Nightmare has transformed once-beautiful creatures into twisted visions. Wraithtalon, once a mighty hippogryph, now preys upon our allies.
The murlocs of Shipwreck Cove have caused more than their fair share of wrecks. Dispose of their Grand Admiral, and the waterways should be safer.

Unknown2: Archmage Vargoth's Travels: Ruins of Nar'thalas
Unknown3: The Nar'thalas Academy was once a place of great learning. Although it is now in ruins, we know Archmage Vargoth visited it recently.

Unknown2: Archmage Vargoth's Travels: The Scholars of Tel'anor
Unknown3: The magical tome we found most likely came from Tel'anor. We may be able to learn more of Archmage Vargoth's travels there if you send a champion.

Unknown2: Archmage Vargoth's Travels: The Forests of Ashenvale
Unknown3: The crystal ball we found in Archmage Vargoth's study was used by Grommash Hellscream. We should send a Champion to investigate its former location in Ashenvale.

Unknown2: Archmage Vargoth's Travels: Best Friends Forever
Unknown3: Zooti Fizzlefury is Archmage Vargoth's closest friend and confidant. Send a champion to Archmage Khadgar's tower in Talador to see if Zooti is still there.
Verdisa of the green dragonflight has asked for our help in capturing roving satyr warbands in Val'sharah. Help take down their foes!
Belgaristrasz of the red dragonflight has contacted us with a plan to retake the Oculus. He needs as many Legion communication devices as can be found.
We will need to boost our power if we are to break through the wards surrounding the Oculus. The Ley Ruins of Zarkhenar are continually spilling out ley energy.
Eternos of the Bronze Dragonflight reports a Legion invasion near the Bronze Dragonshrine in Dragonblight. He requests our aid!
Verdisa, Belgaristrasz, and Eternos are reluctant to return to the Oculus themselves. However, some of their strongest drakes will aid us if we clear the way.
A small demon force has been located in eastern Azsuna, and rumors are that they report directly to Balnazzar. Send our champions to confront them.
An order of priests from the Conclave have been spotted combing the landing site of the Broken Shore, searching for survivors amidst dangerous demons.
The furbolgs of Val'sharah appear to have come under a demonic influence. We must investigate at once.
We've made contact with a tribe of Highmountain tauren. They have an excess supply of furs and leather, but a demon incursion stands in the way.

A small demon force has been located in eastern Aszuna, and rumors are that they report directly to Balnazzar. Send our champions to confront them, and extract any information we can about the dreadlord's location.
The sorcerer Thal'kiel was one of the first Eredar who learned the techniques of summoning and controlling demons. His skull would make a powerful weapon if we can locate it.

Wielded by Sataiel, the first necrolyte, the Deadwind Harvester earned its name by stripping the life from the lands known as Deadwind pass. After centuries locked away, Ulthalesh has been discovered in the posession of the Dark Riders - we must track them down.
We need to find a warlock who excels at summoning greater demons. Scout the hills of Highmountain, keeping an eye out for anyone with potential.
We need to find a warlock who excels at summoning greater demons. Scout within Azsuna, keeping an eye out for anyone with potential.
We need to find a warlock who excels at summoning greater demons. Scout within Val'sharah, keeping an eye out for anyone with potential.
We need to find a warlock who excels at summoning greater demons. Scout within Stormheim, keeping an eye out for anyone with potential.
A group of former Lieutenants of Al'Akir have opposed the rule of the new Windlord. One of them, Mistius, has been particularly violent against the Earthen Ring.
A former Lieutenant of Al'Akir has opposed the rule of the new Windlord. This lieutenant, Zeph, has been setting up multiple ambushes against the Earthen Ring.
A former Lieutenant of Al'Akir has sided with the Burning Legion. This lieutenant, Alacris, must be stopped before he sparks a rebellion from within Skywall.
A former Lieutenant of Al'Akir is seeking to undermine the war effort. This lieutenant, Tulmos, must be defeated before more lives are lost.
PH
Elementalist Janai has requested that we send a strike team to the Firelands to collect Cinderweb eggs for her research.
On a recent expedition to Deepholm, one of our teams recorded strange seismic activity. These were not ordinary tremors... We should investigate further.
The dragon Zeryxia has been slain, but the Twilight's Hammer has not fully abandoned their efforts in Deepholm. We should send a strike team.
The elementals of the Firelands are engaged in an epic battle for supremacy. We must send our Champions to undergo a trial of strength.
The Uncrowned have been established, but we are going to need help.
Lord Ravenholdt has provided a sizeable sum of gold in order to entice Winstone Wolfe to work for the Uncrowned. "The Wolf" is staying at Ravenholdt Manor.
We were attacked by relentless harpies. Defend against the attack and take down their leader.
Andu'talah has fallen to the Nightmare, and Xavius seeks the power of the vessel. He hid a piece of it there. Retrieve it, so we can set a trap for Hakkar.
The spirits at the Temple of a Thousand Lights have stolen a piece of the vessel, and are using it to empower themselves. Take it, so we can set a trap for Hakkar.
Matron Mother Malevolence has supplied you with a list of hard-to-find fel magic apparatuses. They will prove useful.
Belath Dawnblade has asked you to send your Ashtongue warriors to infiltrate the Black Temple. This will prepare you to confront Akama.

Unknown2: Working With the Wardens: Isle of the Watchers
Unknown3: When the Legion invaded the Vault of the Wardens, it wasn't just the Illidari who escaped. Sira Moonwarden has asked for our assistance.
Sira Moonwarden is asking that we hunt down and either capture or kill the satyr known as Skul'vrax. His last known whereabouts were at the Tidal Marsh.

Unknown2: Working With the Wardens: Mellok, Son of Torok
Unknown3: Mellok, Son of Torok is a leader within the new Feltotem tribe, pledging himself to the Legion. The Wardens have asked us to deal with him.
A fel-corrupted storm dragon named Fathnyr occasionally ranges out from its Thorim's Peak aerie. The Wardens have been harassed by the beast.

Unknown2: Working With the Wardens: Mal'Dreth the Corruptor
Unknown3: An eredar named Mal'Dreth the Corruptor convinced several of the Warden adepts to turn traitor and work for the Burning Legion.
A Legion command ship has appeared on the horizon. Send our champions to lead them away from the Wandering Isle!
Even in death, the souls of Azsuna cannot be at peace. Gilamore the Sinister has raised a company of spirit-mages. Stop her, and lay those souls to rest.
On the rocky northern coast of Stormheim, a sea giant has been causing havoc for all ships in the area. We need that coast cleared.
At the base of the Weeping Bluffs, a disturbed water elemental is making it impossible for us to reach the wreckage of our sky-ships.
The Ruined Sanctum stands as a sad reminder of what has been lost to time. Yet its ancient guardian still stands watch. We should put Syphonus to rest.
At the edge of Nightmare, the satyr are spreading their influence right to the doorstep of Malorne's Refuge. Take out their leader, Kalazzius the Guileful.
Few creatures are as tough and resilient as the mountain ettin, and thus, they make the perfect target to test our munitions.
What was once a place of peace has become the realm of nightmare. Dreadful creatures spread darkness and filth through Val'sharah.
The harpies of Highmountain will take any chance they get to harass and curse our allies, and steal our supplies. We should target them in their nests.
Not only do we have a murloc problem, we have a murloc that's stolen vrykul armor. See if you can put a stop to Grrvrgull the Conqueror.
High in the mountains over Stormheim, the matriarch of the Stormwing dragons builds her brood. We should slay her and her spawn.
One of our allies believes that Anax, the giant toad in Suramar, must secrete some kind of useful venom. Seek out Anax, and see what you can find.
Felsoul Hold is churning out infernals almost too fast for us to handle. We should purge their numbers, so the Legion cannot rain them down.
The local tribes have been terrorized by a giant fish lurking in the lakes of Highmountain. It's made off with a few of the fishermen as well.
Among the peaks of Highmountain, a lone ettin has been causing havoc for travelers traveling up the peak. Clear out Oubdob da Smasher.
Our allies have hit a wall of storms in Galebroken Path, likely due to the awakened storm elemental raining down on them. Destroy Bladesquall.
Undead kings and heroes aren't the only thing to worry about in the graveyards of the vrykul. Fjorlag, the Grave's Chill, stalks the living and dead.
Near Moonfall retreat in Suramar, spiders and their ilk have taken over the gardens. We should cut away their webs for our troops in that area.
The once-idyllic gardens of Ambervale are now overrun by withered husks. Among them, Shal'an grows ever more powerful.
A worgen hunter by the name of Houndmaster Ely has taken it upon himself to hunt down the Forsaken, without regard for any chain of command.
A harpy matron, known as Seersei, has been constructing statues of remarkable life-like qualities in the forest of Val'sharah.
Wormtalon harpies have taken over Shadowfen village, and the former residents seek some of their stolen valuables, as well as revenge. Provide both.
While we usually don't mind a sea giant that eats murlocs, Bodash the Hoarder has begun targeting anything that comes close to his home.
Not much can fend off trinket-stealing harpies, but Skullhat, a skull-wearing kobold of the Skywhisker tribe, has managed to hole up in the harpies' hills.
The vrykul infuse their tattoos with ancient magic, and hold their inkbinders in high regard. Destroying them will cripple the vrykul's ability to use that magic.
Outside the walls of Skold-Ashil, a disgraced and fallen shieldmaiden named Lagertha has been plotting to forcefully take her place among the Valkyra.
Dalaran has requested a supply of pristine sand. The best source of this would be from the notorious sand elemental, Beacher.
In Suramar, a vrykul warrior named Hertha Grimdottir has been lying in wait for travelers. Put an end to her.
Once a caretaker of the spirits at Shield's Rest, Runeseer Sigvid has gone mad while the Helejar defile graves. Put him out of his misery.
In the Halls of the Mountain King, the drogbar and vrykul are conducting all manner of strange rituals, harnessing the power of the mountain. Put a stop to it.
Beneath the boughs of Dreadroot, a powerful satyr named Thondrax is harnessing the energies of the Rotwood in order to perform a nightmarish ritual.
The sea giants are notorious for causing shipwrecks, but one in particular will go out of his way to drag any vessel onto the rocky shores of Azsuna.
Kobold legend speaks of a dark, devouring presence deep in the caverns of Highmountain. It is the reason kobolds fear the dark.
The mages of Dalaran have requested a super dense fertilizer. The best material for this comes from the remains of Mac the Bear's meals, found in Azsuna.
The Highmountain tribes cherish the hide of a rare and elusive creature, the Majestic Elderhorn, for their most important ceremonies. Track the beast.
Watching over Skild-Ashil is the Ivory Sentinel, a titan construct made to ward off the unworthy. We must prove that our champions are mightier.

Unknown2: The Dead Exist in the Past
Unknown3: Overlooking Bradensbrook, the malicious ghost of Kiranys Duskwhisper defies any attempt to contain or dislodge him from his vigil.
The Koralune ettin make the gardens of Ambervale their home in Suramar. One has been causing havoc, particularly if someone is an elf.
A satyr named Perrexx has been making sport out of hunting the druids of Moonclaw Vale, as though they were trophies! Turn the tables on him.
The vrykul have employed some unorthodox methods to tame storm drakes. One such tamer is Glimar Ironfist, the drake-wrestler.
The Skyhorn tribe in Highmountain has come under attack from a very large roc named Crawshuk the Hungry. The roc is causing terror in the village.
The war has put a strain on supplies, and the troops crave fresh meat. A gigantic river crab named Tideclaw should provide enough to last them a while.
Even in Dalaran, we must be ever vigilant for threats. The Legion have infiltrated through the sewers and seek to taint the drinking water of the citizens.

Unknown2: Preparations for Invasion: Scouting their Hold
Unknown3: Allari wants you to send your forces to scout Felsoul Hold in Suramar. Once there, they are to identify likely capture targets.
Not everyone has a set of artifact warglaives. If we are to invade a demon world, it would be best if the Illidari received improved weapons.

Unknown2: Preparations for Invasion: Snatch and Grab
Unknown3: Now that the Legion targets at Felsoul Hold have been observed for a while, it is time to send your most capable in to capture them.
It has been many years since the Fel Hammer was in full operational order. Jace needs all hands on deck to help out with some necessary maintenance.

Unknown2: Preparations for Invasion: Where Are the Felsouls?!
Unknown3: With the captured demons safely trapped below deck on the Fel Hammer, Allari is ready to apply her tender mercies and use the Scythe of Souls.
The Knights of the Ebon Blade have been established at Acherus, but we will need allies in our fight against the Legion.  Send Nazgrim to counter this threat.
Now that we have bolstered our numbers, we should display our might and place our troops in the field. The sea giants should be a suitable test of their skill.
We've established Netherlight Temple as a sanctuary, but now it's time to send Calia Menethil to spread the word about its existence and enlist others.
Now that we have recruited some troops, we can use them to bolster our champions' efforts.  Send them out on a routine scouting mission.
The Highmountain tribe have been afraid to leave their homes at night, thanks to a large cat prowling the border of the village.

Unknown2: Artifact: Aluneth, Greatstaff of the Magna
Unknown3: Aluneth was most notably wielded for a time by Aegwynn, the only female Guardian of Tirisfal, although stories indicate that it is far older than she. After passing from her hands, it was eventually locked away in a secret vault, where it remains still.
"Flamestrike" in its native tongue, Felo'melorn was borne into battle by members of the Sunstrider family. Ultimately, the sword was lost in Northrend.

Alodi's greatstaff, Ebonchill, was the bane of many demons in the Legion. After he retired his mantle of Guardian, the staff passed down through his apprentices, eventually lost to time. None know where it resides now, save perhaps Alodi himself.

Unknown2: Throwing SI:7 Off the Trail: Dalaran
Unknown3: If we're going to throw SI:7 off our trail, we need to make a show of it. Let's start some false intrigue on our very own Archmage Khadgar.

Unknown2: Throwing SI:7 Off the Trail: Stormheim
Unknown3: Lady Sylvanas Windrunner has disappeared in Stormheim. Let SI:7 think we are hot on her trail. We are, but we will assign a decoy agent for SI:7 to notice.

Unknown2: Throwing SI:7 Off the Trail: Azsuna
Unknown3: We have a deep contact on the ground in Azsuna. He goes by many names, including Mr. Shackle. Send some people down there to "interfere" with him.

Unknown2: Throwing SI:7 Off the Trail: Highmountain
Unknown3: The Highmountain tribes are outstanding warriors, hunters, and shaman. What they are not is stealthy. Setup surveillance of each tribe's camps.

Unknown2: Throwing SI:7 Off the Trail: Suramar
Unknown3: There is something with the nightborne in Suramar. Unfortunately, their city has too much protection. However, we should let SI:7 see us trying.
A young druid with great potential, Graham Silverclaw, led our scouts to the edge of Suramar. But he ran into a Legion hunting party, and he needs assistance.
Even in the forests of Ashenvale, the satyr, led by Rethazar the Fallen, have been spotted, and they may soon attack outright.
The doom guard Metreon has rallied the satyr of Felwood, and they have attacked Moonglade itself! We cannot allow Moonglade to fall to the Legion.
Those who were once our friends have been claimed by the Nightmare, and the dryad keepers near Andu'talah are among those fallen.
We've received word that Oracle Tidecress, a powerful naga sorceress, has been meeting with the Darkfiend satyr. Slay her and her comrades.
99.0 [reuse me]
[PH]
Priests from all over Azeroth have been aiding our allies on the front lines since the Burning Legion began its invasion. It is time to send in some relief.
Since the days of the Argent Dawn, Light's Hope Chapel has been a beacon of the Light on Azeroth. Travel there and collect a fragment of Light.
The priests of the Exodar have preserved a long tradition of the Light. Collect a fragment from the Exodar, and beware: the Legion may be drawn to it.
Uther the Lightbringer was the first paladin of the Knights of the Silver Hand, and never faltered from his beliefs. His grave is sacred to followers of the Light, but it may also draw evil spirits.
Deep beneath Auchindoun, the naaru D'ore has been regenerating into a being of pure Light once more. Seek out this holy shrine.
The Legion will do everything it can to stop us from revitalizing the wisp, and seek to intercept us before we can collect the last fragment.
In order to fulfill Velen's prophecy, we must infiltrate our enemies and find out if any among them could make a potential ally.
The eredar at Faronaar smith weapons out of lumenstone. Strike at their forges and take the metal we seek, dealing a double blow to our enemies.
The nightborne of Suramar city are studying the properties of lumenstone to augment their constructs. Break into the city and steal their supplies.
Our scouts report that the vrykul have acquired a cache of lumenstone weapons, and they intend to melt them down to create armor for their drakes.
The demons have left lumenstone weapons scattered all over the Broken Shore. If we move fast, we can recover those weapons.
Long ago, a shipment of lumenstone was lost overboard during a terrible storm above Vashj'ir. Unfortunately, the naga may have found it before us.
There are still pockets of the brood queen's forces scattered about below us on Mardum. They could prove a threat to the Fel Hammer.

Unknown2: Where In the World is Mathias?: Obvious Start
Unknown3: The Broken Shore is the obvious location to begin our search for Master Mathias Shaw. We must determine where the Legion is holding him.

Unknown2: Where In the World is Mathias?: Black Rook Hold
Unknown3: Mathias is being moved around. Detheroc is a clever dreadlord. The trail leads to Black Rook Hold. Too bad you did not notice him before.

Unknown2: Where In the World is Mathias?: Altar of End Times
Unknown3: The command center known as the Altar of End Times floats above Faronaar in Azsuna. Break in and have a look around.

Unknown2: Where In the World is Mathias?: Gates of Valor
Unknown3: The Burning Legion has a powerful ally in the vrykul God-King Skovald. Perhaps they are holding Mathias Shaw at the Gates of Valor.

Unknown2: Where In the World is Mathias?: SI:7
Unknown3: We seem to have run out of leads. Time to do the impossible. Time to sneak into SI:7 headquarters and see if Detheroc has left any clues for us.
At the gates of the Hall of Valor, the Felskorn have assembled, including a massive brute named Cleaver Northamel. Slay him, and collect his blood.
The druids at Val'sharah have their hands full with the satyr and the Nightmare. We can help by destroying a rampaging satyr warband, led by Illbringer Zizzifrax.
The Legion has desecrated the sacred burial sites of the Highmountain tribe, raising the bodies of the dead. We should put them back to rest.
In the Felbeast Dens, the Legion creates terrifyingly resilient breeds of manastalkers. We should disrupt their operation by killing Felbreeder Argnotha.
In Felsoul Hold, giant infernals and felbats attack any who come near. Dispose of a few, and collect their blood for our use.
We need to send an emissary to the priests at Netherlight Temple. However, there may be danger along the way. Let us send Maxwell Tyrosus.
Word has reached us that another titan relic may reside in the Halls of Valor, far above Stormheim. We should investigate.
If we are to bring about the return of the Four Horsemen, then we will need to acquire suitable steeds. Send word for Salanar the Horsemen to come to Acherus.

Unknown2: Fallen Steeds: Saddle of the Frozen Crown
Unknown3: Salanar the Horseman requires the saddle of Invincible, the former steed of Arthas Menethil. Since the defeat of Arthas, it has been lost beneath Icecrown.
Salanar the Horseman requires the saddle of Deathcharger, the former steed of Baron Rivendare. Following his defeat, the saddle was returned to Stratholme.

Unknown2: Fallen Steeds: Saddle of the Headless Horseman
Unknown3: Salanar the Horseman requires the saddle used by the great Sir Thomas, the Headless Horseman. The saddle is buried in the cemetery of the Scarlet Monastery.

Unknown2: Fallen Steeds: Saddle of the Huntsman
Unknown3: Salanar the Horseman requires the saddle of Midnight, the steed of Attumen the Huntsman. The saddle should be found somewhere within the ruins of Karazhan.
Salanar the Horseman requires the Shadow Reins used by an ancient Dark Rider. They can only be obtained by defeating one of the Dark Riders directly.
Even in shade form, Xavius can exert his power over Shaladrassil and torments our allies. We should investigate how far the corruption has reached.
The Violet Hold in Dalaran contains some of the most dangerous creatures ever captured. We cannot allow it to fall to the Legion. Investigate!
Even after his fall, Deathwing leaves devastation in his wake. The drogbar have built beneath the mountain, and may have obtained a powerful artifact.
Though she hasn't made an appearance herself, Queen Azshara still controls the naga with an iron will, and is rumored to be after a powerful relic.
Not all vrykul travel to the Halls of Valor. The damned and accursed are rumored to go to the Maw of Souls, a dreadful ship sailing an endless sea.
Suramar City is an architectural marvel, but its reach goes far beyond the glittering spires and avenues above. We should investigate below.
Grand Apothecary Putress was once a trusted advisor to Sylvanas. He deserved his end, but he may still prove useful. Harvest the Essence of Undeath from his soul in the Shadowlands.
Consumed by fear, Grand Empress Shek'zeer spread devastation. Her death was a blessing to the Pandaren... and now to us as well. Harvest the Essence of Fear from her soul in the Shadowlands.
A manipulator and traitor, Soulbinder Nyami wielded powerful shadow magic in life. In death, she is the perfect vessel for the Essence of Shadow. Harvest the essence from her soul in the Shadowlands.
After the death of his son, Admiral Daelin Proudmoore was consumed by the thirst for revenge. Collect the Essence of Hatred from his soul in the Shadowlands.
Once a Gilnean archmage, Arugal unleashed the worgen, and they attacked both friend and foe. Collect the Essence of Darkness from his soul in the Shadowlands.
The dead rise from their graves at Black Rook Hold, and we believe that even long-deceased members of the Ravencrest family walk again.
Even in a time of turmoil, the citizens of Suramar do their best to get on with daily life. However, there may be valuable intel from the Court of Stars.

Unknown2: Investigate the Vault of the Wardens
Unknown3: When Cordana Felsong betrayed the Wardens, Maiev Shadowsong was forced to unleash all prisoners within the Vault. We should investigate.
Val'sharah is being consumed by the Nightmare. Before we can face the darkness, send our forces to investigate the heart of the corruption.
Val'sharah is being consumed by the Nightmare. Before we can face the darkness, send our forces to investigate the heart of the corruption.
Val'sharah is being consumed by the Nightmare. Before we can face the darkness, send our forces to investigate the heart of the corruption.
Val'sharah is being consumed by the Nightmare. Before we can face the darkness, send our forces to investigate the heart of the corruption.
Before we can break our way to the other side, we will need to find the best place to steal a Legion gateway. Felsoul Hold is a candidate.

Unknown2: On the Trail of the Great Worm
Unknown3: Jorhuttam, the great worm, swallowed whole the fabled Gjallerhorn. Send your champions to track the beast!
The demons keep a rich stockpile of weapons at Legion Camp: Ruin in Azsuna. Assault the enemies there and return with any lumenstone that you can find.
The nightborne are moving a large shipment of lumenstone behind the city walls. Invade under cover of darkness and claim the steel for our order!
Our scouts stumbled upon a vrykul raiding party equipped with lumenstone weapons. We can deal a double blow - eliminate the enemy, and take their weapons for our own.
The Broken Shore is littered with debris from battle, with plenty of lumenstone to gather. Just beware of the demons still patrolling the area.
The naga in southern Val'sharah are using weapons crafted from lumenstone. We'll have to convince the naga to part with it.

Unknown2: A More Wretched Hive of Scum and Villainy
Unknown3: To attract new rogues, thieves, and other sundry scoundrels, you need to make Lonika Stillblade an offer she can't refuse. Send Vanessa VanCleef.
The Alliance's intelligence agency, SI:7, has been acting very strange of late. Send our agents into Stormwind City to spy on them and gather intel.
In order to press gang more cutthroats into the ranks of the Uncrowned, Fleet Admiral Tethys wants our finest. A pirate, Yancey Grillsen, would be perfect.
Val'sharah is being consumed by the Nightmare. Before we can face the darkness, send our forces to investigate the heart of the corruption.

The Legion's influence has swept across the Nighthold. Before we can attack the heart of the nightborne stronghold, send our forces to investigate.
As well-intentioned as some warlocks may be, they sometimes get carried away. A pair of warlocks have a fragile containment on a doomlord.
The Tideskorn vrykul pride themselves on their hunting skills, and none more so than Huntress Estrid with her fearsome companion, Halfdan.
Deep in the Bitestone Caverns, a gigantic basilisk has been absorbing the latent power of crystals into its armor.
The Feathermane have recently become hunted. A singing owlcat named Rauren has been tempting the surviving Feathermane kittens away.
The Nightmare has seeped into the waterways of Val'sharah, corrupting even powerful elemental creatures. Pollous the Fetid disrupts the river.
The Soultakers are an organized trio of Helarjar vrykul, intent on plundering the tombs of their own kings. Stop them, before they can do more damage.

Unknown2: The Terror that Flaps in the Day
Unknown3: The Legion breeds felbats as flying mounts for their soldiers, but one in particular has grown so large it darkens the sky with its wings.
Once a librarian of the Kirin Tor, Normantis the Deposed never forgave the damage done by Malygos and the blue flight in Northrend.
Even powerful druids have succumbed to the Nightmare in Shala'nir. One of them, Lyrath Moonfeather, used to embody balance and harmony.
A famous boxing champion in Highmountain has issued a challenge to everyone: Whoever can last three rounds with him will be rewarded handsomely.
A vicious beast, Daggerbeak, has been preying on the equine sunrunners in the open glades of Azsuna. The poor creatures are terrified.

Unknown2: An Apple a Day Keeps the Legion Away
Unknown3: We have reason to suspect that a Legion agent has successfully infiltrated the city of Dalaran, and is now posing as a simple fruit vendor.
A rift has split right through the ley-ruins, discharging dangerous amounts of energy. We should destroy as many ley-creatures as we can.
The Soultakers are an organized trio of Helarjar vrykul, intent on plundering the tombs of their own kings. Stop them, before they can do more damage.

Unknown2: No Matter How Many Times We Tell Them...
Unknown3: The warlocks in Azsuna are at it again, summoning demons they can't possibly hope to control. We can't always fight more fire with fire.
The drogbar have an underground snail-racing ring deep in their caverns. Recently, a vicious fight broke out. We should investigate.
A corrupted Ancient of War, Ironbranch, resides deep in the overrun grove of Shala'nir. Other nightmarish creatures flock to him.
Deep in the vaults of the Arcway, the eredar are stealing knowledge vital to our allies, and they may discover a weakness.
The Soultakers are an organized trio of Helarjar vrykul, intent on plundering the tombs of their own kings. Stop them!
A fel-crazed vrykul warrior has broken through the outer defenses of Dalaran, and made it all the way to Krasus' landing!
Black Rook Hold has been overrun by the spirits of the damned. The long-dead Theryssia rises from her grave, attacking anyone.
Over time, the natural ley energy and mana fields of Suramar have altered the wildlife. Myonix, the matron of the manasabers, is a terrifying beast.
The nightborne have been drawing on the energies of the Starweaver's Sanctum, summoning terrible creatures of pure energy.
The manascale basilisks have been driven out of their caves, and their petrifying gaze is turning anyone - including other wildlife - completely to stone.
The nightborne are slaughtering Moonfall hippogryphs by the flock, and their nests are under attack. We must put a stop to it.
In the heart of Suramar City, some nightborne have embraced the Legion's 'gifts' more readily than others. Miasu must be stopped.
Few beasts are as dangerous and terrifying as Charfeather, an alpha owlcat that does not fear any hunter. Dispose of Charfeather.
A monstrous Withered named Valakar the Thirsty has been drawn to the latent ley-energies of Azsuna, and seeks to consume everything in his path.
The Thistleleaf sprites have been baiting unwary travelers into their groves, by placing what appears to be unguarded treasure right out in the open.
The Hatecoil naga have been capturing sailors off the coast of Azsuna, and forcing them to work for the sea giants of the coves.
The Mak'rana of Azsuna have been riled up by all our activity on the coast, and they're now chopping holes in any ships that come near.
Deep in the walls of Black Rook Hold, even the war sabers have been raised from death. The matriarch Darkshade watches over her unnatural brood.
The Murkwater naga have taken over the ruins of Kal'delar, far too close to our outposts in Val'sharah. We should target their most powerful warriors.
Deep in the forests of Val'sharah, a lone saber has been ambushing any traveler that wanders too close to his den. Hunt down Bahagar.
With our resources stretched thin across the Broken Isles, even the furbolg tribes of Val'sharah are pushing into new territory.
The Nightmare has the wasps into a deadly frenzy. The greatest of the wasps, Mahajik, is large enough to kill with a single sting. Destroy Mahajik.
Perhaps driven out from the hills by his brethren, Gornoth the Lost only knows how to wander and how to kill. We should seek him out and kill him.
Of the same cut as his father, Hill Prince Urgo is destined to be lord of the dangerous hill ettin tribes in Highmountain. We should strike at him.
With all the upheaval in Highmountain, the Ambershard elementals are pouring out of their caverns and threatening the Highmountain tribes.
The Feltotem tribe in Highmountain have bred demonic hounds to serve as guardians. We should cull their numbers.
The Blind Marshlands live up to their name, as thick fog and mist conceal the sad horrors within. We should put the long-dead back to rest.
Deep in the waters of Helheim, a terrifying helsquid named Soulthirster preys on any unfortunate soul to step in the water. Dispatch the squid.
Among Helya's fleet of ships, bearing damned souls on the sea for all eternity, Captain Dargun's crew is among the most feared. Destroy him.
Helya's helhounds are a fearsome pack of predators, but Fenri is a three-headed beast bred for terror and despair. Find him in the depths of Helheim.
For meat, Hannval the Butcher has slaughtered beasts and men for his terrible table. Find him in the hills of Stormheim and put an end to the feast.
In the Field of Forgotten Kings, Oktel Dragonblood no longer rests peacefully in his grave. He was among the first to ride dragons. Defeat him.
Our scouts report that Legion agents have been trying to infiltrate Dalaran through its own citizens. We should investigate and unmask any enemies.
While the mages of Dalaran know to float a city, they sometimes forget about the cracks in the foundation. Latent energy has come to life there.
Late at night, someone has been going to the cemetery in Dalaran and attempting to raise the dead. We should investigate and put a stop to it.
Someone has been shattering windows throughout Dalaran, leaving a trail of destruction and broken glass. Investigate and find the culprit.
Dalaran is no stranger to rats, but they've become even more of a nuisance than usual in the Underbelly. See what's causing all the fuss.
The Valkyra are under attack by Felskorn vrykul. Aid them and crush those who've betrayed Odyn.
Powerful armaments were lost when the great ship Vaesska sank at sea.  Send your armies to retrieve them and strengthen our forces!
A group of mighty warriors loyal to Odyn has been captured by sea giants and are being forced to fight in their underground pit. Free them!
Our scouts report that the Britterbrine came across a cache that may have come from Azshara's treasure room. We should see what we can bring back.
The nightborne pride themselves on the great heights they've achieved with their civilization. Send our champions to their tournament.
At Raven's Glory Arena in Black Rook Hold, our champions can prove their worth and earn respect for our cause. Send them to the Rumble.
The Highmountain tauren have requested our aid to protect their borders from the Feltotem. In return, their ritualists will grant us powerful potions.
Our scouts report that the Legion is experimenting with the properties of Sargeras' own blood, in order to bolster their armies. We should send our champions to acquire the blood for ourselves.
Amalia, famous battle-pet tamer, has a litter of corgi puppies she needs to find homes for! To determine a rightful owner, she's holding a tournament.
Master Tamer Flummox isn't the most conventional pet tamer. Now, he's acquired a firebat pup and means to eat it! Rescue the pup from certain doom.
To train new broken warriors how to deal with the new Burning Legion, Battlelord Gaardoun is requesting that you gather demonic implements.
Felsoul Hold was not suitable for our plans, but there is one other option. Scout out the area around Felblaze Ingress, to see if we have any hope.
The Legion gateway in Felblaze Ingress is the only place powerful enough to take your armies to Niskara. Hymdall will need to wrest it from the Legion first.
Nightborne nobles are planning to hunt an elusive, rare fox, possibly the last of his kind. Send your champions to uncover more information.
According to the Stablemaster, only certain nightborne nobles are invited to the hunt. Send your champions to question Lord Nimrod about the hunt.
After taking Lord Nimrod's hunt invitation, we must discover where the fox hunt will begin. Send your champions to question Lady Dyana on the location.
One last piece of the map remains and you will be ready to stop the nightborne's fox hunt. Send your champions to confront Houndmaster Britomar.
The Hatecoil naga have stirred up the Salteye murlocs, who are now threatening the Ruins of Nar'thalas. They need to be pushed back.
The Llothien grizzlies have voracious appetites, and the cliffwing nest right on the ground. It's too tempting a target for hungry bears.
Though many parts of Val'sharah have been overrun, the corrupted flora may provide valuable insight into the properties of the Nightmare.
The Nightmare has corrupted once-peaceful creatures of the forest, including a herd of stags and does. Put them out of their misery.
There are many paths to the great caverns in Highmountain, but some are more dangerous than others. Explore to see if there's a better way inside.
The Feltotem have poisoned the waterways of Highmountain with their dreadful rituals, sickening the wildlife. Put a stop to it.
Many ships have run aground on the coast of Stormheim, and the sharks are a menace for survivors. Dispose of a few, so the sailors can rebuild.
Hidden in the cliffs of Stormheim, undying spirits keep a watch, despite having long passed on. Bring them some resolution to their vigil.
The Ruins of Falanaar are a dangerous place, especially for any that are wary of arachnids. Thin out the number of Lurkers there.
The forests of Val'sharah have been overrun by Nightmare, and that terror now creeps across into Suramar. Push the satyrs and their defilers back.
On the Timeworn Strand, gigantic turtles wander the ancient ruins. Their meat would go a long way to supporting our troops. Beware of naga though.
In the Lost Orchard, specters brew an arcane-aged wine so awful, it would serve as a decent poison. Disrupt their ghostly operations.
In the shadow of Black Rook Hold, herds of innocent goats have been terrorized by risen hounds. The farmers depend on those goats for their livelihood.
Our scouts report a system of natural caverns beneath Black Rook Hold. We should investigate to see if they are as fortified as the castle above.
The Swamprock murlocs of Shipwreck Cove have a long history of grabbing survivors from wrecks and dragging them back to their village.
The wyrmtongue are scavenging the graves of the Highmountain tauren, courtesy of the Feltotem incursion. Teach them a lesson in respecting the dead.
Usually, the squallhunter drakes prey on the stags of Stormheim, but one stag has turned the tables, slaughtering dragons. Hunt down this beast.
Storm drakes normally live in colonies or are tamed by the vrykul, but one lone drake does neither. Instead, it preys on everyone.
Many Moonfall Acolytes are still trapped after the Nightfallen attacked the Moon Guard Stronghold. Send in some aid for those left behind.
Harpies have moved into the ruins of Tel'anor, destroying the once-beautiful buildings with their foul nests. Dispose of them.
In the Ruins of Llothien, the prowlers have taken over. No one can study or investigate the ruins until their numbers are culled some.
Suramar is split between crumbling ruins and glittering civilization, yet neither is completely safe. Investigate where we can be the most help.
Azsuna's coast is littered with shipwrecks and hazards wrought by its hostile inhabitants. Search for and destroy any lingering threats.
The demons of Faronaar extend their influence deep into Azsuna, corrupting any and all they can. Search, and dispose of any under the Legion's thumb.
The forests of Val'sharah are no place to wander off alone. Danger waits behind every tree, and sometimes it doesn't wait.
The Nightmare has corrupted the roots of Shaladrassil and many creatures within Val'sharah. Seek out and dispose of the crooked elements.
It's not just the pathways of Highmountain that are cause for concern. Some of the greatest threats lie in wait for the unwary.
Scouts report geological instability in Highmountain, where something must be moving just beneath the surface. Investigate and destroy.
Not all vrykul will ascend to the halls of Valarjar, and those are desperate to avoid the turmoil of Helheim. They will do anything to earn honor.
It is said that the Titan watchers themselves observe all the residents of Stormheim, and who is worthy to ascend. Prove our worth.
The nightborne have preserved a culture across thousands of years, but not everything is so civilized and pristine. Investigate what lies beneath.
Despite being half-ruined, the latent energies in Suramar attract creatures of all sorts. Explore the ruins and discover what feeds on this power.
The elven ruins of Azsuna hold secrets we can't begin to comprehend. Search and rediscover what has been lost to time.
The denizens of Azsuna, whether natural or unnatural, are a dangerous sort. Be wary while traveling through the area.
The nights in Val'sharah are filled with the howls of disturbed creatures. Investigate the cause and put them out of their misery.
Creatures in Val'sharah were hardly tame before the Nightmare crept in, and corrupting energies have made them even more dangerous.
Though mostly covered in rocky hills and snowy cliffs, Highmountain also has its forests, with their own beauties and dangers.
The tauren of Highmountain have learned to live with the perilous landscape, but more than just cliffs and peaks endanger the tribes.
Not only the vrykul threaten anyone who enters the hills of Stormheim. Sometimes danger strikes from the sky.
Dangers creep from the Helmouth, and even the dead are not safe in their graves. Investigate Stormheim and fight back against death itself.
Demons simply don't know when they're beaten. Even now, they plot to invade parts of Suramar. Investigate, and stop them.
Demons simply don't know when they're beaten. Even now, they plot to invade parts of Suramar. Investigate, and stop them.
Should give you a huge success chance boost, if it's the first mission of the day. Also should give you a cool item!
Lucian from One Last Glass was overheard lamenting the loss of a shipment of extraodinarly stinky cheese.  Apparently the courier was overrun as he made his way through the Underbelly.
There was once a great stock of wine in Falanaar.  Send some troops to investigate and see what they can find.
Karazhan stirs. Send our forces to investigate the tower.
There's nothing quite like the thrill of defending the honor of your faction and engaging in some friendly, or not so friendly, competition. Send your champion to explore the battlegrounds.
The melee continues in the battleground. Send our forces to assist the cause.
There's nothing quite like the sound of the crowd cheering as you deftly maneuver and muscle for rank. Send your champions to the arenas to see what they can learn.
Your champions have heard of a place of endless war, where the tides of battle flow constantly. Send them to investigate further.
A young druid with great potential, Graham Silverclaw, led our scouts to the edge of Suramar. But he ran into a Legion hunting party, and he needs assistance.
Salanar the Horseman requires the Shadow Reins used by an ancient Dark Rider. They can only be obtained by defeating one of the Dark Riders directly.
Once a Gilnean archmage, Arugal unleashed the worgen, and they attacked both friend and foe. Collect the Essence of Darkness from his soul in the Shadowlands.
